    "We then use the transposed versions of temporal convolution layers as in c to upsample the features.",
    "The resulting features are mapped to the speech parameters using the same structure as shown in b. Non-causal versions apply temporal attention to past, present and future tokens, whereas the causal version applies temporal attention only to past and present tokens.",
    "e, The ECoG decoder using LSTM layers.",
    "We use three LSTM layers and one layer of channel MLP to generate features.",
    "We then reuse the prediction layers in b to generate the corresponding speech parameters."
